<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="ISO-8859-1">
<title>AngularJS Basics</title>
</head>
<body ng-app="myApp" ng-controller="myCtrl">

	<!-- Angular extends HTML with ng-directives
	
	The ng-app directive defines your AngularJS app
	
	AngularJS Expressions: {{ }} to print out model
	to the page
	
	2 way data-binding: updates the view and the model
	data at the same time
	
	Custom Directive: an html tag or attribute that can
	inject its own HTML
	
	the ng-model directive binds the value of HTML controls
	(input, select, etc) to our app data
	
	Data model - A collection of dtata available for our application
	
	HTML view - html container where AngularJS app is displayed.
	The view has access to the model, and there are serveral ways
	of displaying model data in the view.

 -->
 
 <h1>AngularJS - JavaScript MVC Framework</h1>
 <div id="hello world"></div>

	<input type="text" data-ng-model="whatever" placeholder="Type something here" />
	<p>{{whatever}}</p>
	<br>
	<h3 ng-bind="whatever"></h3>
	<br>
	<p> Here is an expression {{ 10 + 10 }}</p>
	<br>
	<h2> Some more cool binding stuff:</h2><br>
<!-- data-ng-model is the same as ng-model -->
	<input style="background:{{myCol}}" ng-model="myCol" placeholder="Enter a color" value="red">
	<input type="number" style="background:#{{myCol2}}" ng-model="myCol2" placeholder="Enter a hex number">
	
	<br>
	<h3>Intro to controllers:</h3>
	First name: <input type="text" ng-model="fn" /><br>
	Last name: <input type="text" ng-model="ln" /><br>
	
	<script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/angularjs/1.6.4/angular.min.js"></script>
	<script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/angularjs/1.6.4/angular-route.js"></script>
	<script src="JS/app.js"></script>
	
</body>
</html>